I.	INTRODUCTION
Amplification is an important operation in many analog and sometimes even in digital circuits. Usually amplification of a signal is needed because its amplitude may be too 
small to drive a load, have good noise margin, or provide certain logic level in a digital system. Amplification is also important for a feedback system. 

